<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <head><persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                            Marsh</persName></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-08-09"><hi rend="italic">August</hi>
                                9, 1871.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Marsh</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Rome:</hi></p>
                    <p>Referring to article twelve of the treaty with Great Britain of 8th May, the
                        President and Her Majesty the Queen of Great Britain have conjointly agreed
                        to receive Count <pb facs="0694" n="480" xml:id="pg_480"/> Corti as the
                        third commissioner, to be appointed under that article, if the Italian
                        government consent to his serving. You will see your British colleague, and
                        arrange with him for a contemporaneous request to the Italian government for
                        its consent, and inform Department of answer by telegraph.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>